this is the start of the command - buyearth, earth orbs is the stock item we'll be using for this tutorial, now need to add stockprice and amount ints
[code]int amount = Integer.parseInt(command.substring(9));
int stockcost = 50000; //price per stock[/code]
when someone trys to buy stock it will be like this ::buyearth (amountofstock) the int amount is the part of the command (amountofstock)
stockcost is how much each stock costs - 50000 you can edit this next we need some requirements
[code]if(playerHasItem(995, amount*stockcost) && amount <= 10000)[/code]
if(playerHasItem...etc is making sure the player has the amount times the stockcost, so they can buy the right amount for the right price
amount <= 10000, ive found if someone trys to buy more than around 100000 the server either laggs or nulls, this might be differnt for other servers, so be free to remove or change the buy requirement. next we need to add and delete some items
[code]deleteItem(995, amount*stockcost);
addItem(576, amount);[/code]
deleteitem takes the amount your trying to buy times the stock cost out of you inventory
additem adds the stock, and the amount of the stock next we should, but dont have to add confirmation message
[code]sM("You invest "+amount*stockcost+" in "+amount+" Earth stocks.");
sM("Say ::sellearth (amount) to sell - they do not have to be in noted form");[/code]
the first message tells the player how much they invested in how many stocks
the second message tells the player how to sell their stock - we'll get to that in a sec
next we need to add the error messages
